The BetterLinks command was at attempt to fix a lack of flexibility in YAG's built in link rule.

If the channel name has a number in it, the link will be ignored. This allows users to send links in ticket channels, which in my server, are the only channels with numbers.

Set the trigger to regex. The following regex will trigger when any domain name in the list is detected.
^*\.com$*|^*\.gg$*|^*\.net$*|^*\.org$*|^*\.play$*|^*\.co$*|^*\.biz$*|^*\.info$*|^*\.jobs$*|^*\.mobi$*|^*\.name$*|^*\.ly$*|^*\.tel$*|^*\.email$*|^*\.tech$*|^*\.xyz$*|^*\.codes$*|^*\.biz$*|^*\.ca$*|^*\.cn$*|^*\.fr$*|^*\.ch$*|^*\.au$*|^*\.in$*|^*\.de$*|^*\.jp$*|^*\.nl$*|^*\.uk$*|^*\.mx$*|^*\.no$*|^*\.ru$*|^*\.br$*|^*\.se$*|^*\.es$*|^*\.us$*

There is also an option to set a whitelisted domain. If the message contains this domain, it will be ignored.
It is set up to only delete messages containing violations, but you can add your own warnings or other punishments with exec or execAdmin.
